summary: This is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection TECS Person Encounter List detailing the travel history of Ghislaine Maxwell from 1990 to 1999. The document, generated in 2020, lists 58 international flight entries and exits, primarily between the U.S. (JFK, MIA) and Europe (London, Paris), showing her frequent international travel during the period of the alleged conspiracy.

keyFacts: The document is a government-generated travel log showing Ghislaine Maxwell's extensive international movements between 1990 and 1999.
It lists 58 separate flight encounters, primarily between JFK/Miami and London/Paris, indicating a pattern of frequent transatlantic travel.
The document was generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on January 16, 2020, suggesting it was compiled for investigative or legal purposes related to the Epstein case.
Travel documents used include Alien Registration Card (A), Passport (P), and INSPASS (I), showing her use of multiple travel authorizations.
The data provides a timeline of Maxwell's physical presence in key locations (New York, Florida, London, Paris) during the period central to the allegations against her and Jeffrey Epstein.
